entry.title: Wait until TestV4DatabaseFactory is ready
entry.content:
Take 2 on trying to make sure TestV4DatabaseFactory is ready before being used.



Cannot reproduce as it is very rare, will commit possible fixes and see how it

works on the bots. It should not make things worse as worst case will time out

instead of crash with nullptr.



Ideally this while loop should be in v4_test_util, but it cannot use content/public,

all uses are either directly from safe browsing tests, or indirectly through

TestSafeBrowsingDatabaseHelper so once the right fix is found it should be

possible to contain it to SafeBrowsing code.



Even more ideally, TestV4DatabaseFactory::MarkPrefixAsBad should wait until

ready and return a callback when done. This would require changing the callers

and is probably out of scope.

entry.content:
The original fix for spelling and grammar text

decoration overflow did not invalidate overflow

when markers were added and deleted (the tests passed

invalidating overflow when the markers are added or

removed for any reason. It also simplifies the code

for target-text, and addresses potential problems

when markers are moved between nodes and when a node

does not have computed style.

entry.title: Support batch operations of the TabRestoreService in Recent Tabs
entry.content:
Prior to this CL, RecentTabsMediator took care to not process web state

list batch changes, but only for the current regular web state list.

But the TabRestoreService can get new entries from other web state

lists:

- The inactive web state list.

- Every other window, i.e. the web state lists from other windows.



Prior to this change, closing all inactive tabs could block the main

thread. With this change, no longer.



Before: https://drive.google.com/open?id=13Af5Lu_kXQ9uPMS4m55l9Muxlip8Hb7J

entry.title: Improve IntersectionObservation::CanUseCachedRects
entry.content:
The change is behind blink feature IntersectionOptimization which will

include more intersection observer optimizations mostly related to

scrolls.



The improvements are:

1. Allow use of cached rects when the root and the target are under

the same scrollable context (i.e. no user/programmatically

scrollable scrollers between the root and the target). Previously

CanUseCachedRects returned false in the case.

2. Fix a problem about overflow:hidden scrollers. Previously

overflow:hidden was not treated as scrollable while it can scroll

programmatically.

3. Fix a problem that CanUseCachedRects() doesn't follow the containing

block order when finding enclosing scrollers.

entry.title: Keep sending honey pot messages until we turn on web contents.
entry.content:
This is a high priority change, the bug this fixes is stopping

all JAWS 2021 users from being able to access web contents.



With some Windows 11 features causing kNativeAPIs to be

turned on after startup, our honeypot code was no longer

being triggered. Since there are many other ways to turn

on accessibility this was not noticed until recently.

This change updates our logic to no longer consider the

fact that some accessibility has been enabled as an

indication that we no longer should fire the honey pot

event.



With this change we will continue to send honey pot events

until web contents accessibility has been turned on. The

honey pot will trigger web contents accessibility, and at

that point will no longer fire.



Bug: 1450993

entry.title: Improve first frame painting when stalled.
entry.content:
The situation in which we're stalled and waiting for the best frame to

paint should be very rare and unfortunately the stall signal isn't

reliable on Android. As such just wait ~250ms to paint the first frame

if we don't yet have the best one.



We'll still kick off the size metadata checks as soon as possible to

avoid layout shift though.



R=liberato
